<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="152" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1164,2055]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,528,1236,1262]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
LM Description (
<figureCitation box="[399,520,1236,1262]" captionStart="FIGURE 1–60" captionStartId="2.[136,229,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,187,1389]" captionTargetId="figure-26@2.[196,1391,187,1389]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1–60. Light microscope images of Platessa arborea sp. nov. Valves representing the size diminution series. 1–30. Raphesternum valve, and 31–60. Sternum valve. Scale bar: 10 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6690984" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6690984/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Figs 1–60</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
:—Valve elliptical with narrowly rounded apices. Raphe-sternum valve (RSV): Length: 6.5–9.5 µm, width: 3.5–4.5 µm, ratio length/width: 1.6–2.2 (n = 60). Axial area narrow and hardly discernible, visible only near center of the valve; central area nearly rectangular shape, bordered by 2–3 shorter striae frequently more widely spaced. Striae radiate throughout the valve, 
<quantity box="[777,877,1344,1370]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.842" metricValueMax="6.096" metricValueMin="5.588" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" unit="in" value="23.0" valueMax="24.0" valueMin="22.0">22–24 in</quantity>
10 µm. Raphe slightly filiform expanded proximal raphe endings.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1164,2055]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
Sternum valve (SV): wide axial area, Length: 6.0–9.0 µm, width: 3.5–4.5 µm. Striae densely arranged 
<quantity box="[1352,1452,1416,1442]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.842" metricValueMax="6.096" metricValueMin="5.588" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" unit="in" value="23.0" valueMax="24.0" valueMin="22.0">22–24 in</quantity>
10 µm, parallel at centre, radiate towards apices.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1164,2055]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,545,1488,1514]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
SEM Description (
<figureCitation box="[408,537,1488,1514]" captionStart="FIGURE 61–67" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1780,1802]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,190,1755]" captionTargetId="figure-26@4.[151,1435,190,1755]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 61–67. Platessa arborea sp. nov. SEM. 61. External view of the whole valve (Raphe-sternum valve) showing the striae arrangement and rectangular axial area at the middle of the valve. 62. External view of the whole valve (Sternum valve) showing the broad axial area at the center and biseriate striae near the mantle. 63. External view of apices showing the hooked proximal raphe ends and distal raphe end deflection. 64. Internal view of apices showing the proximal and distal raphe ends curvature and deflection. 65. Internal view of the whole valve (Raphe-sternum valve) showing the opposite deflection of both raphe ends and distal raphe ends with prominent helictoglossae. 66–67. Internal view of the whole valve (Sternum valve) showing the wide axial area and raised interstriae. Scale bars: = 1 μm (Figs 61–67)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6690992" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6690992/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Figs 61–67</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
:—Raphe-sternum valve (RSV): Externally, raphe filiform, slight curvature found near ends (
<figureCitation box="[264,425,1524,1551]" captionStart="FIGURE 61–67" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1780,1802]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,190,1755]" captionTargetId="figure-26@4.[151,1435,190,1755]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 61–67. Platessa arborea sp. nov. SEM. 61. External view of the whole valve (Raphe-sternum valve) showing the striae arrangement and rectangular axial area at the middle of the valve. 62. External view of the whole valve (Sternum valve) showing the broad axial area at the center and biseriate striae near the mantle. 63. External view of apices showing the hooked proximal raphe ends and distal raphe end deflection. 64. Internal view of apices showing the proximal and distal raphe ends curvature and deflection. 65. Internal view of the whole valve (Raphe-sternum valve) showing the opposite deflection of both raphe ends and distal raphe ends with prominent helictoglossae. 66–67. Internal view of the whole valve (Sternum valve) showing the wide axial area and raised interstriae. Scale bars: = 1 μm (Figs 61–67)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6690992" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6690992/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Figs 61 &amp; 63</figureCitation>
). Proximal raphe ends positioned in a broadened shallow groove, distal raphe located in the shallow groove with cone-shaped endings, and both ends slightly bend to the same side (
<figureCitation box="[1194,1279,1560,1587]" captionStart="FIGURE 61–67" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1780,1802]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,190,1755]" captionTargetId="figure-26@4.[151,1435,190,1755]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 61–67. Platessa arborea sp. nov. SEM. 61. External view of the whole valve (Raphe-sternum valve) showing the striae arrangement and rectangular axial area at the middle of the valve. 62. External view of the whole valve (Sternum valve) showing the broad axial area at the center and biseriate striae near the mantle. 63. External view of apices showing the hooked proximal raphe ends and distal raphe end deflection. 64. Internal view of apices showing the proximal and distal raphe ends curvature and deflection. 65. Internal view of the whole valve (Raphe-sternum valve) showing the opposite deflection of both raphe ends and distal raphe ends with prominent helictoglossae. 66–67. Internal view of the whole valve (Sternum valve) showing the wide axial area and raised interstriae. Scale bars: = 1 μm (Figs 61–67)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6690992" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6690992/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
). Striae mostly uniseriate; however found biseriate at 2–3 striae near apices. (
<figureCitation box="[824,906,1596,1623]" captionStart="FIGURE 61–67" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1780,1802]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,190,1755]" captionTargetId="figure-26@4.[151,1435,190,1755]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 61–67. Platessa arborea sp. nov. SEM. 61. External view of the whole valve (Raphe-sternum valve) showing the striae arrangement and rectangular axial area at the middle of the valve. 62. External view of the whole valve (Sternum valve) showing the broad axial area at the center and biseriate striae near the mantle. 63. External view of apices showing the hooked proximal raphe ends and distal raphe end deflection. 64. Internal view of apices showing the proximal and distal raphe ends curvature and deflection. 65. Internal view of the whole valve (Raphe-sternum valve) showing the opposite deflection of both raphe ends and distal raphe ends with prominent helictoglossae. 66–67. Internal view of the whole valve (Sternum valve) showing the wide axial area and raised interstriae. Scale bars: = 1 μm (Figs 61–67)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6690992" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6690992/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
). Areolae, apically slit-like throughout the valve, only at the center of the valve it is round-shaped towards axial area (
<figureCitation box="[903,986,1632,1659]" captionStart="FIGURE 61–67" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1780,1802]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,190,1755]" captionTargetId="figure-26@4.[151,1435,190,1755]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 61–67. Platessa arborea sp. nov. SEM. 61. External view of the whole valve (Raphe-sternum valve) showing the striae arrangement and rectangular axial area at the middle of the valve. 62. External view of the whole valve (Sternum valve) showing the broad axial area at the center and biseriate striae near the mantle. 63. External view of apices showing the hooked proximal raphe ends and distal raphe end deflection. 64. Internal view of apices showing the proximal and distal raphe ends curvature and deflection. 65. Internal view of the whole valve (Raphe-sternum valve) showing the opposite deflection of both raphe ends and distal raphe ends with prominent helictoglossae. 66–67. Internal view of the whole valve (Sternum valve) showing the wide axial area and raised interstriae. Scale bars: = 1 μm (Figs 61–67)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6690992" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6690992/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1164,2055]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
Internally, proximal raphe ends are strongly hooked, a very remarkable feature which is infrequent in other 
<taxonomicName pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
<emphasis box="[1356,1451,1668,1694]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Platessa</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, and its distal ends are curved on opposite sides, terminating in well-developed helictoglossae (
<figureCitation box="[1306,1439,1704,1731]" captionStart="FIGURE 61–67" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1780,1802]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,190,1755]" captionTargetId="figure-26@4.[151,1435,190,1755]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 61–67. Platessa arborea sp. nov. SEM. 61. External view of the whole valve (Raphe-sternum valve) showing the striae arrangement and rectangular axial area at the middle of the valve. 62. External view of the whole valve (Sternum valve) showing the broad axial area at the center and biseriate striae near the mantle. 63. External view of apices showing the hooked proximal raphe ends and distal raphe end deflection. 64. Internal view of apices showing the proximal and distal raphe ends curvature and deflection. 65. Internal view of the whole valve (Raphe-sternum valve) showing the opposite deflection of both raphe ends and distal raphe ends with prominent helictoglossae. 66–67. Internal view of the whole valve (Sternum valve) showing the wide axial area and raised interstriae. Scale bars: = 1 μm (Figs 61–67)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6690992" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6690992/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Figs 64, 65</figureCitation>
). Striae lowered between raised virgae. Width of the interstriae is wider than the striae. Striae internally rectangular to round in shape and mostly covered with hymen (
<figureCitation box="[727,862,1776,1803]" captionStart="FIGURE 61–67" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1780,1802]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,190,1755]" captionTargetId="figure-26@4.[151,1435,190,1755]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 61–67. Platessa arborea sp. nov. SEM. 61. External view of the whole valve (Raphe-sternum valve) showing the striae arrangement and rectangular axial area at the middle of the valve. 62. External view of the whole valve (Sternum valve) showing the broad axial area at the center and biseriate striae near the mantle. 63. External view of apices showing the hooked proximal raphe ends and distal raphe end deflection. 64. Internal view of apices showing the proximal and distal raphe ends curvature and deflection. 65. Internal view of the whole valve (Raphe-sternum valve) showing the opposite deflection of both raphe ends and distal raphe ends with prominent helictoglossae. 66–67. Internal view of the whole valve (Sternum valve) showing the wide axial area and raised interstriae. Scale bars: = 1 μm (Figs 61–67)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6690992" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6690992/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Figs 64, 65</figureCitation>
). An apparent depression is observed on the central nodule (
<figureCitation box="[231,369,1812,1839]" captionStart="FIGURE 61–67" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1780,1802]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,190,1755]" captionTargetId="figure-26@4.[151,1435,190,1755]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 61–67. Platessa arborea sp. nov. SEM. 61. External view of the whole valve (Raphe-sternum valve) showing the striae arrangement and rectangular axial area at the middle of the valve. 62. External view of the whole valve (Sternum valve) showing the broad axial area at the center and biseriate striae near the mantle. 63. External view of apices showing the hooked proximal raphe ends and distal raphe end deflection. 64. Internal view of apices showing the proximal and distal raphe ends curvature and deflection. 65. Internal view of the whole valve (Raphe-sternum valve) showing the opposite deflection of both raphe ends and distal raphe ends with prominent helictoglossae. 66–67. Internal view of the whole valve (Sternum valve) showing the wide axial area and raised interstriae. Scale bars: = 1 μm (Figs 61–67)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6690992" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6690992/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Figs 64, 65</figureCitation>
). Sternum valve (SV), externally, axial area covered with several irregular shape depressions distributed on the surface of the valve (
<figureCitation box="[573,657,1848,1875]" captionStart="FIGURE 61–67" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1780,1802]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,190,1755]" captionTargetId="figure-26@4.[151,1435,190,1755]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 61–67. Platessa arborea sp. nov. SEM. 61. External view of the whole valve (Raphe-sternum valve) showing the striae arrangement and rectangular axial area at the middle of the valve. 62. External view of the whole valve (Sternum valve) showing the broad axial area at the center and biseriate striae near the mantle. 63. External view of apices showing the hooked proximal raphe ends and distal raphe end deflection. 64. Internal view of apices showing the proximal and distal raphe ends curvature and deflection. 65. Internal view of the whole valve (Raphe-sternum valve) showing the opposite deflection of both raphe ends and distal raphe ends with prominent helictoglossae. 66–67. Internal view of the whole valve (Sternum valve) showing the wide axial area and raised interstriae. Scale bars: = 1 μm (Figs 61–67)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6690992" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6690992/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
). Striae uniseriate, however, found biseriate at more than 10 striae near the valve mantle (
<figureCitation box="[336,420,1884,1911]" captionStart="FIGURE 61–67" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1780,1802]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,190,1755]" captionTargetId="figure-26@4.[151,1435,190,1755]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 61–67. Platessa arborea sp. nov. SEM. 61. External view of the whole valve (Raphe-sternum valve) showing the striae arrangement and rectangular axial area at the middle of the valve. 62. External view of the whole valve (Sternum valve) showing the broad axial area at the center and biseriate striae near the mantle. 63. External view of apices showing the hooked proximal raphe ends and distal raphe end deflection. 64. Internal view of apices showing the proximal and distal raphe ends curvature and deflection. 65. Internal view of the whole valve (Raphe-sternum valve) showing the opposite deflection of both raphe ends and distal raphe ends with prominent helictoglossae. 66–67. Internal view of the whole valve (Sternum valve) showing the wide axial area and raised interstriae. Scale bars: = 1 μm (Figs 61–67)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6690992" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6690992/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
). Interstriae is raised, and the width of striae is unequal (
<figureCitation box="[1050,1134,1884,1911]" captionStart="FIGURE 61–67" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1780,1802]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,190,1755]" captionTargetId="figure-26@4.[151,1435,190,1755]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 61–67. Platessa arborea sp. nov. SEM. 61. External view of the whole valve (Raphe-sternum valve) showing the striae arrangement and rectangular axial area at the middle of the valve. 62. External view of the whole valve (Sternum valve) showing the broad axial area at the center and biseriate striae near the mantle. 63. External view of apices showing the hooked proximal raphe ends and distal raphe end deflection. 64. Internal view of apices showing the proximal and distal raphe ends curvature and deflection. 65. Internal view of the whole valve (Raphe-sternum valve) showing the opposite deflection of both raphe ends and distal raphe ends with prominent helictoglossae. 66–67. Internal view of the whole valve (Sternum valve) showing the wide axial area and raised interstriae. Scale bars: = 1 μm (Figs 61–67)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6690992" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6690992/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
). Internally, axial area is flat and features are not easily visible (
<figureCitation box="[526,610,1920,1947]" captionStart="FIGURE 61–67" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1780,1802]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,190,1755]" captionTargetId="figure-26@4.[151,1435,190,1755]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 61–67. Platessa arborea sp. nov. SEM. 61. External view of the whole valve (Raphe-sternum valve) showing the striae arrangement and rectangular axial area at the middle of the valve. 62. External view of the whole valve (Sternum valve) showing the broad axial area at the center and biseriate striae near the mantle. 63. External view of apices showing the hooked proximal raphe ends and distal raphe end deflection. 64. Internal view of apices showing the proximal and distal raphe ends curvature and deflection. 65. Internal view of the whole valve (Raphe-sternum valve) showing the opposite deflection of both raphe ends and distal raphe ends with prominent helictoglossae. 66–67. Internal view of the whole valve (Sternum valve) showing the wide axial area and raised interstriae. Scale bars: = 1 μm (Figs 61–67)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6690992" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6690992/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Fig. 66</figureCitation>
). Biseriate striae found near the mantle with hymenated areolae. Interstriae raised its width slightly more than the striae (
<figureCitation box="[642,726,1956,1983]" captionStart="FIGURE 61–67" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1780,1802]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,190,1755]" captionTargetId="figure-26@4.[151,1435,190,1755]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 61–67. Platessa arborea sp. nov. SEM. 61. External view of the whole valve (Raphe-sternum valve) showing the striae arrangement and rectangular axial area at the middle of the valve. 62. External view of the whole valve (Sternum valve) showing the broad axial area at the center and biseriate striae near the mantle. 63. External view of apices showing the hooked proximal raphe ends and distal raphe end deflection. 64. Internal view of apices showing the proximal and distal raphe ends curvature and deflection. 65. Internal view of the whole valve (Raphe-sternum valve) showing the opposite deflection of both raphe ends and distal raphe ends with prominent helictoglossae. 66–67. Internal view of the whole valve (Sternum valve) showing the wide axial area and raised interstriae. Scale bars: = 1 μm (Figs 61–67)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6690992" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6690992/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Fig. 67</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
